Examples 2

Source: vignettes/Examples2.Rmd
Examples2.Rmd
library(aggrid)
library(dplyr)
#> 
#> Attaching package: 'dplyr'
#> The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
#> 
#>     filter, lag
#> The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
#> 
#>     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
library(htmlwidgets)

Selection

Row Selection

CheckboxSelection 

head(iris, n = 10) |>
  aggrid(checkboxSelection = T)

Single Selection 

head(iris, n = 10) |>
  aggrid(checkboxSelection = T,rowSelection = "single",suppressRowClickSelection = T)

selectedRows 

head(iris, n = 10) |>
  aggrid(checkboxSelection = T,selectedRows = 1:3)

selectedRows all

I set a convenience parameter for selecting all rows.

head(iris, n = 10) |>
  aggrid(checkboxSelection = T,selectedRows = "all")

Sparkline

line plot and column plot 

mtcars |>
  dplyr::group_by(cyl) |>
  dplyr::summarize(mpg_line = list(mpg)) |>
  aggrid() |>
  ag_col_render(mpg_line, cellRenderer = "agSparklineCellRenderer")

Note in the snippet above that specifying an agSparklineCellRenderer will display the data using the default line sparkline.

Sparklines are customised by supplying sparklineOptions to the cellRendererParams on the Sparkline Cell Renderer as shown below. For exampleï¼š

bar plot 

head(mtcars, n = 10) |>
  dplyr::mutate(mpg_plot = mpg / max(mpg)) |>
  dplyr::select(cyl, mpg_plot) |>
  aggrid() |>
  ag_col_render(mpg_plot,
    cellRenderer = "agSparklineCellRenderer",
    cellRendererParams = list(
      sparklineOptions = list(
        type = "bar",
        valueAxisDomain = c(0, 1)
      )
    )
  )
#> Warning: By default htmlwidgets set auto_unbox = TRUE so the 1 length atomic elements
#> are not send as array. So default set `valueGetter` to convert Number to Array.

Row group 

aggrid(iris) |>
  ag_col_def(Species, rowGroup = T)

Accessories

statusBar

Default has statusBar, you can set it FALSE use ag_gridOptions():

aggrid(iris) |>
  ag_gridOptions(statusBar = FALSE)

Side Bar 

aggrid(iris) |>
  ag_gridOptions(sideBar = TRUE)

Custom Side bar:

aggrid(iris) |>
  ag_gridOptions(sideBar = list(
    toolPanels = list(
      list(
        id = "columns",
        labelDefault = "Columns",
        labelKey = "columns",
        iconKey = "columns",
        toolPanel = "agColumnsToolPanel"
      )
    )
  ))

Charts 

aggrid(iris) |> 
  enable_charts()
